            </div>
            <div class="ml-4">
              <h4 class="text-lg leading-6 font-medium text-gray-900">Compete with Others</h4>
              <p class="mt-2 text-base text-gray-700">
                We provide practice problems in the form of CTF (capture-the-flag) challenges. Competitors solve problems in 
                various categories e.g. SOCMINT, GEOINT, etc. and receive points for solved challenges. These points are then 
                used to determine rankings on a global leaderboard!
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="p-6 bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg">
          <div class="flex">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 text-3xl text-pink-600">
              <i class="fa-solid fa-brain"></i>
            </div>
            <div class="ml-4">
              <h4 class="text-lg leading-6 font-medium text-gray-900">Learn Techniques</h4>
              <p class="mt-2 text-base text-gray-700">
                Along with practice problems, we provide educational modules consisting of guides, lectures, and videos for you to learn 
                topics from scratch. For every practice problem, we have a module covering a corresponding topic.

                <i>Coming Soon</i>
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="p-6 bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg">
          <div class="flex">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 text-3xl text-yellow-500">
              <i class="fa-solid fa-bolt-lightning"></i>
            </div>
            <div class="ml-4">
              <h4 class="text-lg leading-6 font-medium text-gray-900">Beginner-Friendly</h4>
              <p class="mt-2 text-base text-gray-700">
                No matter what your skill level is, we promise to have challenges for you! Regardless of whether you're just getting started with OSINT 
                or have years of experience under your belt, there are challenges for everyone.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
